          "body": "Verse 20 is one of the most theologically dense images in the Pentateuch: the same pillar of cloud that gave Israel *light* was *darkness* to Egypt. One revelation, two responses, two destinies. This becomes a pattern throughout Scripture: the same gospel that is the aroma of life to those being saved is the aroma of death to those perishing (2 Corinthians 2:15-16); the same Christ who is a cornerstone to the believer is a stone of stumbling to the disobedient (1 Peter 2:7-8); the same sea that is dry ground for Israel is grave for Egypt. The chapter refuses neutral ground. The pillar of God's presence separates the two camps absolutely — and what determines which side you are on is which side of the LORD's covenant you have come to stand on."
